[% META title = 'Theme Mappings Handling in Git Pull' %]
[% PageVersion = 'admin/theme_mappings_handling.tt,v 0.01 2025/01/19 shanta Exp shanta ' %]
[% debug %]
[% IF c.session.debug_mode == 1 %]
    [% PageVersion %]
    [% "Debugging HostName: " _ HostName %]
    [%# INCLUDE 'debug.tt' %]
[% END %]

<div class="documentation-content">
    <h1>Theme Mappings Handling in Git Pull</h1>

    <section class="overview">
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>The Comserv system has been enhanced to automatically handle changes to the <code>theme_mappings.json</code> file during Git pull operations. This feature is particularly useful for production servers where local theme configurations may differ from the repository version.</p>
        
        <div class="alert alert-info">
            <strong>Latest Theme System Updates</strong>: See <a href="/Documentation/changelog/2025-01-19-css-theme-system-enhancements.tt">CSS Theme System Enhancements - January 2025</a> for comprehensive improvements to theme management including interactive CSS editor and enhanced admin controls.
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="how-it-works">
        <h2>How It Works</h2>
        <p>When you use the Admin Git Pull feature, the system will:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Detect if you have local changes to <code>theme_mappings.json</code></li>
            <li>Create a backup of your local version at <code>theme_mappings.json.bak</code></li>
            <li>Stash your changes using Git's stash functionality</li>
            <li>Pull the latest changes from the repository</li>
            <li>Attempt to reapply your local changes automatically</li>
            <li>Provide clear feedback about the process</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="benefits">
        <h2>Benefits</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Preserves Local Customizations</strong>: Your site-specific theme mappings are preserved</li>
            <li><strong>Reduces Merge Conflicts</strong>: Handles the common conflict scenario automatically</li>
            <li><strong>Provides Safety Nets</strong>: Creates backups before any operations</li>
            <li><strong>Improves Workflow</strong>: No need to manually stash/unstash or resolve conflicts</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="handling-conflicts">
        <h2>Handling Conflicts</h2>
        <p>If there are conflicts between your local changes and the repository version:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>The system will notify you with a warning message</li>
            <li>Your original file is preserved as <code>theme_mappings.json.bak</code></li>
            <li>You can manually resolve the conflict by:
                <ul>
                    <li>Editing the current file to merge changes</li>
                    <li>Restoring from the backup if needed</li>
                    <li>Using Git's conflict resolution tools</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="best-practices">
        <h2>Best Practices</h2>
        <p>While this feature helps manage theme configuration conflicts, consider these best practices:</p>
        <ol>
            <li><strong>Database Storage</strong>: For a more robust solution, consider moving theme mappings to the database</li>
            <li><strong>Environment Configuration</strong>: Use environment-specific configuration files that are excluded from Git</li>
            <li><strong>Documentation</strong>: Document any production-specific theme mappings for reference</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="troubleshooting">
        <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
        <p>If you encounter issues with the automatic handling:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Check the backup file at <code>Comserv/root/static/config/theme_mappings.json.bak</code></li>
            <li>View the Git stash with <code>git stash list</code> to see if your changes were saved</li>
            <li>Apply the stash manually with <code>git stash apply</code> if needed</li>
            <li>Check the application logs for detailed error messages</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="future-enhancements">
        <h2>Future Enhancements</h2>
        <p>Future versions may include:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Database-driven theme configuration</li>
            <li>Environment-specific configuration files</li>
            <li>Web interface for managing theme mappings</li>
            <li>More sophisticated conflict resolution</li>
        </ol>
    </section>
</div>